2026-04-20 19:08:12 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['timing potentiometer (ambient sensor module)', 'sensitivity potentiometer (ambient sensor module)'] hypothesis_explanation='All functional circuit components (relay, comparator, sensor, resistors, indicator) measure nominal values and operation, and there is no visible physical damage nor polarity inversion in wiring. Adjusting either timing or sensitivity potentiometer causes the circuit to become unstable or oscillate, and both potentiometers are visually set to their maximum (1.0), which is strongly correlated with circuit instability. In some comparator circuits, if both potentiometers are set to extreme values, the feedback loop or bias network may cause instability and sustained oscillation rather than simple thresholding behavior. Therefore, a dual fault (misadjustment or internal fault) of the sensitivity and/or timing potentiometers is most likely causing instability in the sensor module comparator circuit, resulting in the observed relay oscillation and lamp blinking.'
