2026-04-20 19:08:27 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['ambient sensor module ground connection (internal wiring, PCB trace, or shared terminal)'] hypothesis_explanation='The continuity test for ground connections within the ambient sensor module does not show near-zero resistance as expected for a proper ground (typical would be close to 0 Ω). Instead, a resistance of approximately 5000 Ω was found between the sensor and all relevant ground lines. This is abnormally high, and would explain the unstable behavior and oscillation of the comparator, relay, and system as a whole. A high-impedance ground can cause the reference voltage to float, resulting in random relay triggers and comparator instability, manifesting as periodic and unpredictable cycling of the lamp. The root cause may be a loose ground wire, failed PCB trace, poor solder joint, or corrosion at a shared terminal inside the ambient sensor module.'
